cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SD

The paper introduces a new data-driven precipitation prediction model using Deep Learning methodology, specifically Convolutional LSTM. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of LSTM and Convolutional Neural Networks (CNN) in the model also suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with weather data and forecasting, which could also place it in the Scientific Computing and Numerical Analysis (cs.SD) sub-category.
